Items.

Use items to list visible non-living objects in your current room.

This command is useful when you want to hear only the objects in the room,
without NPCs, players, exits, or the room description.

Common forms:

items
  List visible items in the room.

look <item>
  Look more closely at one item from the list.

get <item>
  Pick up an item, if it can be taken.

put <item> in <container>
  Put an item into a visible container, if allowed.

If several visible items have the same name, the command condenses them and
gives a count.
